cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of neural network models for predicting users' level of stress using location information collected by smartphones. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on mental health monitoring and intervention, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the use of mobile sensing technologies and contextual information for quantifying individuals' mood and wellbeing can be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and trade-offs involved in building machine learning models for digital mental health, which can be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
